        "text": "<p data-aid=\"168180215\" id=\"p_kLq3p\">\u201cWe must put God in the forefront of everything else in our lives. He must come first. \u2026<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"168180229\" id=\"p_oig0Y\">\u201cWhen we put God first, all other things fall into their proper place or drop out of our lives. Our love of the Lord will govern the claims for our affection, the demands on our time, the interests we pursue, and the order of our priorities\u201d (<cite><a class=\"cross-ref\" href=\"/study/manual/teachings-of-presidents-of-the-church-ezra-taft-benson/chapter-1-the-great-commandment-love-the-lord?lang=eng&amp;id=p19-p20#p19\">Teachings of Presidents of the Church: Ezra Taft Benson<\/a><\/cite> [2014], 40). See also Dallin H. Oaks, \u201c<a class=\"cross-ref\" href=\"/study/general-conference/2007/10/good-better-best?lang=eng\">Good, Better, Best<\/a>,\u201d <cite>Ensign<\/cite> or <cite>Liahona<\/cite>, Nov. 2007, 104\u20138.<\/p>",
        "referenceUris": [
          {
            "href": "/study/manual/teachings-of-presidents-of-the-church-ezra-taft-benson/chapter-1-the-great-commandment-love-the-lord?lang=eng&amp;id=p19-p20#p19",
