      "note28": {
        "marker": "28.",
        "context": "",
        "pid": "168180055",
        "id": "note28",
        "text": "<p data-aid=\"168180464\" id=\"p_bgjsx\">\u201c<em>Hesed<\/em> is a special kind of love and mercy that God feels for and extends to those who have made a covenant with Him. And we reciprocate with <em>hesed<\/em> for Him.<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"168180477\" id=\"p_uef3O\">\u201cBecause God has <em>hesed<\/em> for those who have covenanted with Him, He will love them. He will continue to work with them and offer them opportunities to change. He will forgive them when they repent. And should they stray, He will help them find their way back to Him.<\/p>\n<p data-aid=\"168180489\" id=\"p_oy9cI\">\u201cOnce you and I have made a covenant with God, our relationship with Him becomes much closer than before our covenant\u201d (Russell M. Nelson, \u201c<a class=\"cross-ref\" href=\"/study/liahona/2022/10/04-the-everlasting-covenant?lang=eng&amp;id=p12-p14#p12\">The Everlasting Covenant<\/a>,\u201d <cite>Liahona<\/cite>, Oct. 2022, 6).<\/p>",
        "referenceUris": [{
          "href": "/study/liahona/2022/10/04-the-everlasting-covenant?lang=eng&amp;id=p12-p14#p12",
          "text": "The Everlasting Covenant",
          "type": "cross-ref"
        }]
      }
    }
  }
